We can create React component n Two Ways
1. React.createClass() {}
2. React.Component {}  // import React, {Component} from 'react';
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Simple React Class Structure : -
class Xyz extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props); // when we need to use this.props then only
    }
      render() {
        return();
      }
    }
}
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Super() : - Super() is used to pass whatever is being inherited from Parent Class.
it is used in child class to claa the methods of Parent Class.
Note : Private Methods of Parent/Super Class can not be claaed.
-------------------------------------------------------------------
If we are using constructor in any Class, it is mandatory to pass super().
-------------------------------------------------------------------
You should use super(props) when you need to use this.props, otherwise use super().
--------------------------------------------------------------------
Statefull Components : - These are always class components. 
e.g : -
class Xyz extends Component {
  render() {
    return(
      <div>Hello React</div>
    );
  }
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
